4a8740e1-6ac8-4136-8709-28323abe33f0-d1c.content: t"When a user sends a message and the receiving client is either offline or online but in another tab, then when the client comes back online or returns to the room, the number of unseen messages should be shown next to the sender's username.  Example: If there are two users, A and B — and A sends messages to B, but B is either offline or in another tab — then when B logs back in or comes into the room, next to A’s username, there should be a green dot (in the middle right corner), and inside that dot, the number of unread messages should be shown — for example, 3 if 3 messages are unseen.  Once B views all the messages, the green dot should automatically disappear.  Also, when a user sees the message, the sender should also get some indication that their message was seen — please add something like that too.

But when I click on the client's username, all the messages automatically get marked as seen, and after that, they are no longer shown as unseen — please fix this.  Also, when a message is sent and the other user is offline, there should be a single tick in white color.  If the user is online but hasn't seen the message yet, then there should be a double tick in white color.  And when the user sees the message, the double tick should automatically change to dark blue color.  Please add this — and when a message is seen, its status should automatically update.  Example: If A and B are users, and A sends a message while B is offline → A should see a single white tick. If B comes online → it should become a double white tick. And when B sees the message → it should turn into a double dark green (or blue) tick automatically.
